<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="336" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[813,1451,289,344]" pageId="21" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,956,289,313]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="336">Etymology. –</emphasis>
The name of this species refers to the trilobed posterior abdominal gland.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[813,1451,385,472]" pageId="21" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,1119,385,409]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="336">Phylogenetic relationships. –</emphasis>
The relationships of this species are unresolved beyond inclusion within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1965" box="[1314,1451,417,440]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divergens">
<emphasis box="[1314,1451,417,440]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="336">S. divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="336" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[813,1452,513,632]" pageId="21" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,1241,513,537]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="336">Distribution and seasonal occurrence. –</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[1246,1343,513,536]" name="Thailand" pageId="21" pageNumber="336">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. A species with a wide distribution: Northeast to South 
<collectingCountry box="[1286,1381,545,568]" name="Thailand" pageId="21" pageNumber="336">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1395,1448,545,568]" country="Thailand" name="Loei" pageId="21" pageNumber="336">Loei</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[813,874,577,600]" country="Thailand" name="Krabi" pageId="21" pageNumber="336">Krabi</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[928,1029,577,600]" country="Thailand" name="Songkhla" pageId="21" pageNumber="336">Songkhla</collectingRegion>
provinces). Records in the North from May, October in the South.
</paragraph>
